  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2173",
  "title": "\"Hide results on init\" example breaks URL sync",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nA bug\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nI use the example code from the documentation: https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/documentation/#hide-results-on-init\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar search = instantsearch({\r\n  [...],\r\n  searchFunction: function(helper) {\r\n    var searchResults = $('.search-results');\r\n    if (helper.state.query === '') {\r\n      searchResults.hide();\r\n      return;\r\n    }\r\n    helper.search();\r\n    searchResults.show();\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere is a JSFiddle: https://jsfiddle.net/4jqgawpk/3/\r\n\r\nOpen the HTML iframe: https://fiddle.jshell.net/4jqgawpk/3/show/ (please try in Firefox, somehow the URL is not updated in Chrome, probably because of JSFiddle)\r\n\r\nType a search, wait for the URL params to update\r\n\r\nEmpty the search box\r\n\r\nThe URL params are not reset, the last search query is still there.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nWhen I empty the search box, I expect the URL to be \"clean\" (at least the `q` param should be empty).\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\n\r\nFirefox latest, Chrome latest\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the proposed solution?**\r\n\r\nThere should probably be a way to use the JS helper to reset the URL params. If possible, the example from the documentation should be updated to use it.",
